## ☁️ AWS EC2 Instance Configuration

The project was deployed on an **AWS EC2 Ubuntu Server** with the following configuration:

| Configuration | Value |
|--------------|-------|
| Operating System | Ubuntu Server |
| Instance Type | t3.micro |
| Root Volume | **20 GB** (gp3) |
| Region | eu-north-1 |
| Access Method | SSH |

> **Note:** I configured the EC2 root volume with **20 GB** of storage instead of the default size. This provided sufficient disk space for installing **Jenkins**, **Docker**, plugins, Docker images, containers, and Jenkins workspaces without running into storage limitations.

