## 🐳 Jenkins and Docker Integration

To enable Jenkins pipelines to execute Docker commands, I integrated Jenkins with Docker by granting the Jenkins user permission to access the Docker daemon.

### Configuration Steps

1. Install Docker.
2. Start and enable the Docker service.
3. Add the Jenkins user to the Docker group.
4. Restart both Docker and Jenkins services.
5. Verify that Jenkins can execute Docker commands.

```bash
sudo usermod -aG docker jenkins
sudo systemctl restart docker
sudo systemctl restart jenkins
sudo -u jenkins docker ps
```

After completing these steps, Jenkins was able to build Docker images and manage Docker containers directly from pipeline jobs.

